<IN>
CDS, INTEREST RATES, COMMERCIAL PAPER (FIN)
BANKS (BNK)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- The average interest rate rose to 8.0099% at
Citicorp's $50 million weekly auction of 91-day commercial
paper, or corporate IOUs, from 7.861% at last week's sale.
   Bids totaling $415.6 million were submitted. Accepted bids
ranged from 8.005% to 8.01%.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Citicorp also said the average rate rose to 8.039% at its
$50 million auction of 182-day commercial paper from 7.764%
at last week's sale.
   Bids totaling $380 million were submitted. Accepted bids
ranged from 8.03% to 8.04%.
   The bank holding company will auction another $50 million
in each maturity next Tuesday.
