   Japan's Wholesale Prices Rise
</HL>
<DATE>
08/22/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   JAPAN
</CO>
<LP>
   TOKYO -- Japan's wholesale prices rose 0.2% in the first
10 days of August from the previous 10-day period, and
increased 0.9% from the previous year, the Bank of Japan
reported.
   The wholesale price index stood at 90.5 at the end of the
ten days. The index's base of 1985 prices equals 100.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Domestic prices climbed 0.1% from the previous ten days
and rose 0.4% from a year earlier.
   In July, wholesale prices rose 0.4% from the previous
month and 0.5% from a year earlier, the central bank reported
last week.
