<HL>
   International Brief -- Canon Inc.:
   Unconsolidated Pretax Profit
   For First Half Jumped 67%
</HL>
<DATE>
08/22/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C10
</SO>
<CO>
   CANNY
</CO>
<IN>
OFFICE EQUIPMENT (OFF)
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Canon Inc. of Japan reported that unconsolidated pretax
profit for the first half jumped 67% to 37.65 billion yen
($275.2 million) from 22.53 billion yen a year earlier.
   Net income increased 57% to 20.15 billion yen, or 27.17
yen a share, from 12.8 billion yen, or 20.41 yen a share.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Supported by strong demand for color copiers, laser
printers and high-quality cameras, sales climbed 22% to
455.49 billion yen from 374.5 billion yen.
   Exports, which accounted for 73% of total sales, increased
24% from a year earlier, as shipments to all destinations
showed healthy growth, a Canon official said. Domestic sales
also did well, rising 16%. Mainline copier sales increased
20% to 147.92 billion yen, the official said.
Computer-related equipment sales grew 27% to 125.79 billion
yen.
