   Bank, Four Partners Form
   An Investment Company
</HL>
<DATE>
08/22/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   T.CM H.CKH GE J.MIB J.NKT WNEWS
</CO>
<LP>
   Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce said it and four
partners have committed $100 million to form a Hong
Kong-based investment company.
   The Toronto-based bank said newly formed CEF New Asia
Partners Ltd. is seeking additional investors to increase its
capital to as much as $250 million over the next six months.
</LP>
