<LP>
   CF INCOME PARTNERS LIMITED PARTNERSHIP (Los Angeles) --
Jeffrey H. Lynford, 42 years old, was named president and
chief executive officer of CF Management Corp., the general
partner of CF Income. He succeeds R. Craig Overturf, 55, who
resigned. Mr. Lynford was named vice chairman, chief
financial officer and co-chief executive in June. He
continues as chief financial officer until a successor is
named; the vice chairman title will be dropped, a spokeswoman
said. Mr. Lynford is chairman of Wellsford Group Inc., an
affiliate of New York-based Wellsford Capital Partners
Limited Partnership, which acquired 20% of CF Management in
December. CF Partners is a real estate investment concern.
